      "updated_at": "2018-12-13T12:01:57.418Z",
      "cooked": "<p>When I use the right oscillator for scrolling animation, it can become pretty wobbly at slow speeds.</p>\n<p>I\u2019m still getting to know the vidiot, so I\u2019m wondering if this is normal behavior or not?</p>\n<p>example:<br>\n</p><div class=\"lazyYT\" data-youtube-id=\"e3roeEtw1Ck\" data-youtube-title=\"C0010\" data-width=\"480\" data-height=\"270\" data-parameters=\"feature=oembed&amp;wmode=opaque\"></div>\n<p>(edit: it seems to be connected to what speed the left oscillator is set to, even though I\u2019m not using that oscillator for anything)</p>",
      "like_count": 0,
      "reply_to_post_number": null,
      "is_wiki": false
    },
    {
      "id": 3317,
      "post_number": 2,
      "username": "creatorlars",
      "name": "Lars Larsen",
      "created_at": "2018-12-18T00:32:43.296Z",
      "updated_at": "2018-12-18T00:32:43.296Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Seems like an odd issue \u2013 occasionally wobbly drifting speed is normal, but the little jumps you\u2019re seeing here aren\u2019t something I\u2019d expect.  Is this with nothing patched?</p>",
